#MEM id=examples source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Finance/felix/skills/executive-operations/saas-economics-efficiency-metrics/examples/healthy-unit-economics.md
M|examples|**Company:** CloudAnalytics (mid-market business intelligence SaaS)
M|examples|**Stage:** Series B growth stage
M|examples|**Customer Base:** 500 accounts, 12,000 users
M|examples|**Period:** Q2 2024
M|examples|```
M|examples|Quarterly Revenue: $6,000,000
M|examples|COGS:
M|examples|- AWS hosting & infrastructure: $600,000
M|examples|- Payment processing (2.5%): $150,000
M|examples|- Customer onboarding: $150,000
M|examples|Total COGS: $900,000
M|examples|Gross Profit: $5,100,000
M|examples|Gross Margin: 85% ✅
M|examples|```
M|examples|```
M|examples|SMB:
M|examples|- S&M Spend: $200K/quarter
M|examples|- New Customers: 50
M|examples|- CAC: $4,000
M|examples|Mid-Market:
M|examples|- S&M Spend: $400K/quarter
M|examples|- New Customers: 40
M|examples|- CAC: $10,000
M|examples|Enterprise:
M|examples|- S&M Spend: $300K/quarter
M|examples|- New Customers: 10
M|examples|- CAC: $30,000
M|examples|Blended CAC: $9,000
M|examples|```
M|examples|```
M|examples|SMB:
M|examples|- ARPU: $250/month
M|examples|- Monthly Churn: 3%
M|examples|- Gross Margin: 82%
M|examples|- LTV: ($250 × 82%) / 3% = $6,833
M|examples|Mid-Market:
M|examples|- ARPU: $1,200/month
M|examples|- Monthly Churn: 2%
M|examples|- Gross Margin: 85%
M|examples|- LTV: ($1,200 × 85%) / 2% = $51,000
M|examples|Enterprise:
M|examples|- ARPU: $5,000/month
M|examples|- Monthly Churn: 1%
M|examples|- Gross Margin: 88%
M|examples|- LTV: ($5,000 × 88%) / 1% = $440,000
M|examples|Blended LTV: $45,000
M|examples|```
M|examples|```
M|examples|SMB: $6,833 / $4,000 = 1.7:1 ⚠️ (marginal)
M|examples|Mid-Market: $51,000 / $10,000 = 5.1:1 ✅ (excellent)
M|examples|Enterprise: $440,000 / $30,000 = 14.7:1 ✅ (outstanding)
M|examples|Blended: $45,000 / $9,000 = 5:1 ✅
M|examples|```
M|examples|```
M|examples|SMB: $4,000 / ($250 × 82%) = 19.5 months ⚠️
M|examples|Mid-Market: $10,000 / ($1,200 × 85%) = 9.8 months ✅
M|examples|Enterprise: $30,000 / ($5,000 × 88%) = 6.8 months ✅
M|examples|Blended: 11 months ✅
M|examples|```
M|examples|```
M|examples|Monthly Expenses:
M|examples|- S&M: $300,000
M|examples|- R&D: $400,000
M|examples|- G&A: $150,000
M|examples|- COGS: $300,000
M|examples|Gross Burn: $1,150,000/month
M|examples|Monthly Revenue: $2,000,000
M|examples|Net Burn: -$850,000/month (profitable! ✅)
M|examples|Cash Balance: $25,000,000
M|examples|Runway: Infinite (profitable)
M|examples|```
M|examples|```
M|examples|Annual Revenue: $24M
M|examples|OpEx:
M|examples|- S&M: $3.6M (15% of revenue) ✅
M|examples|- R&D: $4.8M (20% of revenue) ✅
M|examples|- G&A: $1.8M (7.5% of revenue) ✅
M|examples|Total OpEx: $10.2M (42.5% of revenue)
M|examples|Net Income: $24M - $3.6M - $10.2M = $10.2M
M|examples|Profit Margin: 42.5% ✅
M|examples|```
M|examples|```
M|examples|Revenue Growth Rate: 45% YoY
M|examples|Profit Margin: 42.5%
M|examples|Rule of 40 = 45% + 42.5% = 87.5 ✅ (outstanding!)
M|examples|```
M|examples|```
M|examples|Q2 Revenue: $6M
M|examples|Q1 Revenue: $5.2M
M|examples|Increase: $800K
M|examples|Q1 S&M Spend: $850K
M|examples|Magic Number: ($800K × 4) / $850K = $3.2M / $850K = 3.76 ✅ (excellent!)
M|examples|```
M|examples|| Quarter | Revenue | Rev Growth | OpEx | OpEx Growth | Leverage |
M|examples||---------|---------|------------|------|-------------|----------|
M|examples|| Q3 2023 | $4.5M | - | $2.2M | - | - |
M|examples|| Q4 2023 | $5.0M | 11% | $2.4M | 9% | Positive ✅ |
M|examples|| Q1 2024 | $5.2M | 4% | $2.5M | 4% | Neutral |
M|examples|| Q2 2024 | $6.0M | 15% | $2.55M | 2% | Positive ✅ |
M|examples|**Analysis:** Revenue growing faster than OpEx = positive operating leverage.
M|examples|**Outstanding unit economics:**
M|examples|- 5:1 blended LTV:CAC (healthy range: 3-5:1)
M|examples|- 11-month blended payback (target: <12 months)
M|examples|- 85% gross margin (well above 70% SaaS benchmark)
M|examples|- Mid-market and enterprise segments have stellar economics
M|examples|**Profitable growth:**
M|examples|- 42.5% profit margin (exceptional for growth-stage SaaS)
M|examples|- Rule of 40 = 87.5 (nearly double the 40 threshold)
M|examples|- Infinite runway (profitable, no burn)
M|examples|**Efficient go-to-market:**
M|examples|- Magic number = 3.76 (well above 0.75 threshold)
M|examples|- For every $1 in S&M spend, generating $3.76 in new ARR
M|examples|- Positive operating leverage (revenue growing faster than costs)
M|examples|**Segment optimization:**
M|examples|- Enterprise: 14.7:1 LTV:CAC, 7-month payback (amazing)
M|examples|- Mid-market: 5.1:1 LTV:CAC, 10-month payback (excellent)
M|examples|- SMB: 1.7:1 LTV:CAC, 19.5-month payback (marginal)
M|examples|**SMB segment underperformance:**
M|examples|- 1.7:1 LTV:CAC is below 3:1 threshold
M|examples|- 19.5-month payback is concerning
M|examples|- Contributing to blended metrics, but dragging them down
M|examples|**Potential actions:**
M|examples|1. **Reduce SMB CAC** (improve conversion, shorten sales cycle)
M|examples|2. **Increase SMB LTV** (reduce churn, add expansion paths)
M|examples|3. **Deprioritize SMB** (shift budget to mid-market/enterprise)
M|examples|**Channel allocation:**
M|examples|- Enterprise has 14.7:1 LTV:CAC but only 10 new customers/quarter
M|examples|- Could scale enterprise acquisition more aggressively
M|examples|**Why:** 14.7:1 LTV:CAC and 7-month payback = massive opportunity.
M|examples|**Actions:**
M|examples|- Increase enterprise S&M budget from $300K to $500K/quarter
M|examples|- Hire 2 enterprise AEs
M|examples|- Target 20 enterprise logos/quarter (up from 10)
M|examples|**Expected impact:**
M|examples|- Additional $200K/quarter S&M spend
M|examples|- 10 additional enterprise customers
M|examples|- 10 × $30K CAC = $300K investment
M|examples|- 10 × $440K LTV = $4.4M in LTV created
M|examples|- Net value creation: $4.1M
M|examples|**Why:** 1.7:1 LTV:CAC is marginal; 19.5-month payback strains cash (even though profitable overall).
M|examples|**Option A: Optimize SMB**
M|examples|- Reduce CAC through self-serve onboarding (target $2K CAC)
M|examples|- Improve retention to 2% monthly churn (boost LTV to $10,250)
M|examples|- New LTV:CAC: 5.1:1 (healthy)
M|examples|**Option B: Exit SMB**
M|examples|- Stop SMB acquisition, reallocate $200K/quarter to mid-market/enterprise
M|examples|- Focus on higher-quality segments with better economics
M|examples|**Recommendation:** Try Option A for 2 quarters. If LTV:CAC doesn't improve to >3:1, exit SMB.
M|examples|**Why:** 42.5% profit margin + 45% growth is exceptional. Don't sacrifice this.
M|examples|**Actions:**
M|examples|- Continue positive operating leverage (revenue growth > cost growth)
M|examples|- Maintain Rule of 40 >40 (ideally >60)
M|examples|- Reinvest profits strategically in highest-ROI channels
M|examples|**Current blended magic number:** 3.76 (excellent)
M|examples|**Calculate by segment:**
M|examples|- If enterprise magic number is 5+, scale aggressively
M|examples|- If SMB magic number is <0.5, consider exiting
M|examples|**Growth targets:**
M|examples|- [ ] Reach $36M ARR (50% YoY growth)
M|examples|- [ ] Maintain >40% profit margin
M|examples|- [ ] Rule of 40 >70
M|examples|**Unit economics targets:**
M|examples|- [ ] Blended LTV:CAC remains >4:1
M|examples|- [ ] Blended payback remains <12 months
M|examples|- [ ] SMB LTV:CAC improves to >3:1 or exit segment
M|examples|**Efficiency targets:**
M|examples|- [ ] Magic number remains >2.0
M|examples|- [ ] Positive operating leverage every quarter
M|examples|- [ ] S&M efficiency: <20% of revenue
M|examples|This is a model SaaS business:
M|examples|- Profitable AND growing (rare combination)
M|examples|- Exceptional unit economics (5:1 LTV:CAC, 11-month payback)
M|examples|- Highly efficient GTM (3.76 magic number)
M|examples|- Strong balance (Rule of 40 = 87.5)
M|examples|**Main opportunity:** Scale enterprise aggressively while optimizing or exiting SMB segment. The business can sustain aggressive growth without burning cash.